@node Overview
@section Overview

The Xeetapus API is available at the following base URLs:

@table @asis
@item Development
@code{http://localhost:8080/api}

@item Production
@code{https://your-domain.com/api}
@end table

All API endpoints are relative to this base URL.  For example, the
login endpoint at @code{POST /api/auth/login} would be accessed as
@code{http://localhost:8080/api/auth/login} in development.

@node Authentication
@section Authentication

The API uses cookie-based authentication with JWT tokens.  To
authenticate, you must first obtain a session cookie through the login
endpoint.  The browser will then automatically include this cookie in
subsequent requests.

@subheading Obtaining a Session

Send a POST request to @code{/api/auth/login} with valid credentials.
Upon success, the server will set a @code{session} cookie:

@example
POST /api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

@{"username":"user","password":"password"@}
@end example

The response will include a @code{Set-Cookie} header containing the
session token.

@subheading CSRF Protection

For state-changing requests (POST, PUT, DELETE), you must include a
CSRF token in the @code{X-CSRF-Token} header.  The CSRF token is
returned in the response body from @code{/api/auth/me}:

@example
X-CSRF-Token: 1712345678:abc123...:def456...
@end example

The CSRF token is signed and expires after 24 hours.

@node Response Format
@section Response Format

All API responses are JSON objects.

@subheading Success Response

Successful responses have the following structure:

@verbatim
@{
  "data": @{...@},
  "status": "success"
@}
@end verbatim

For responses that return a single object, the object is returned
directly as the value of the @code{data} field.

@subheading Error Response

Error responses have the following structure:

@verbatim
@{
  "error": "Error message describing what went wrong",
  "status": "error"
@}
@end verbatim

@node HTTP Status Codes
@section HTTP Status Codes

The API uses standard HTTP status codes to indicate the result of a
request.

@table @asis
@item 200 OK
The request succeeded.

@item 201 Created
The request succeeded and a new resource was created.

@item 204 No Content
The request succeeded.  No response body is returned (used for
successful deletions).

@item 400 Bad Request
The request was malformed or contained invalid parameters.

@item 401 Unauthorized
Authentication is required or the provided credentials are invalid.

@item 403 Forbidden
The server understood the request but refuses to fulfill it.  This may
indicate a CSRF validation failure or insufficient permissions.

@item 404 Not Found
The requested resource does not exist.

@item 409 Conflict
The request conflicts with existing data (e.g., duplicate username).

@item 429 Too Many Requests
The rate limit has been exceeded.  See @ref{Rate Limiting}.

@item 500 Internal Server Error
An unexpected error occurred on the server.
@end table

@node Rate Limiting
@section Rate Limiting

The API enforces rate limits to prevent abuse.  By default, clients are
limited to 100 requests per 60-second window per IP address.

@subheading Rate Limit Headers

Every response includes headers indicating the current rate limit
status:

@table @asis
@item X-RateLimit-Limit
The maximum number of requests allowed in the window.

@item X-RateLimit-Remaining
The number of requests remaining in the current window.

@item X-RateLimit-Reset
The Unix timestamp when the window will reset.
@end table

@subheading When Rate Limited

When a client exceeds the rate limit, the server returns a @code{429
Too Many Requests} response:

@verbatim
@{
  "error": "Rate limit exceeded. Please try again later.",
  "status": "error"
@}
@end verbatim

Wait until the @code{X-RateLimit-Reset} timestamp before making
additional requests.

@node Pagination
@section Pagination

Endpoints that return lists support pagination through query parameters.

@table @asis
@item page
The page number to retrieve.  Defaults to 1.

@item limit
The number of items per page.  Defaults to 20, maximum 100.
@end table

@example
GET /api/posts?page=2&limit=50
@end example

Paginated responses include metadata about the current page and total
available pages:

@verbatim
@{
  "data": [...],
  "page": 2,
  "total_pages": 10,
  "status": "success"
@}
@end verbatim

@node Auth Endpoints
@section Authentication Endpoints

@deffn POST /api/auth/register
Register a new user account.
@end deffn

@subheading Request Body

@table @asis
@item username
String.  Required.  3 to 20 characters.  May contain letters, numbers,
and underscores.  Must start with a letter.

@item email
String.  Required.  A valid email address.

@item password
String.  Required.  At least 8 characters.  Must contain at least one
uppercase letter, one lowercase letter, and one digit.
@end table

@subheading Response

Returns the newly created user object with status @code{201 Created}.

@example
@{
  "id": 1,
  "username": "johndoe",
  "email": "john@@example.com",
  "created_at": "2024-01-15T10:30:00Z"
@}
@end example

@subheading Errors

@table @asis
@item 400
Invalid input data.

@item 409
Username or email already exists.
@end table

@deffn POST /api/auth/login
Authenticate a user and create a session.
@end deffn

@subheading Request Body

@table @asis
@item username
String.  Required.  The user's username.

@item password
String.  Required.  The user's password.
@end table

@subheading Response

Returns the authenticated user object.  A @code{session} cookie is set.

@example
@{
  "id": 1,
  "username": "johndoe",
  "email": "john@@example.com",
  "display_name": "John Doe",
  "bio": "Developer",
  "avatar_url": null,
  "created_at": "2024-01-15T10:30:00Z"
@}
@end example

@subheading Errors

@table @asis
@item 401
Invalid username or password.
@end table

@deffn POST /api/auth/logout
End the current session.
@end deffn

@subheading Authentication

Requires authentication.

@subheading Response

Returns a success message.  The @code{session} cookie is cleared.

@deffn GET /api/auth/me
Get the currently authenticated user.
@end deffn

@subheading Authentication

Requires authentication.

@subheading Response

Returns the authenticated user object, including the CSRF token.

@example
@{
  "id": 1,
  "username": "johndoe",
  "email": "john@@example.com",
  "display_name": "John Doe",
  "bio": "Developer",
  "avatar_url": null,
  "csrf_token": "abc123...",
  "created_at": "2024-01-15T10:30:00Z"
@}
@end example

@node User Endpoints
@section User Endpoints

@deffn GET /api/users/@{username@}
Get a user's public profile.
@end deffn

@subheading Authentication

Not required.

@subheading Response

@example
@{
  "id": 1,
  "username": "johndoe",
  "display_name": "John Doe",
  "bio": "Software developer",
  "avatar_url": null,
  "followers_count": 150,
  "following_count": 200,
  "posts_count": 50,
  "created_at": "2024-01-15T10:30:00Z"
@}
@end example

@deffn POST /api/users/@{username@}/follow
Follow a user.
@end deffn

@subheading Authentication

Requires authentication.

@deffn DELETE /api/users/@{username@}/follow
Unfollow a user.
@end deffn

@subheading Authentication

Requires authentication.

@deffn PUT /api/users/me
Update the current user's profile.
@end deffn

@subheading Authentication

Requires authentication.

@subheading Request Body

@table @asis
@item display_name
String.  Optional.  The user's display name.

@item bio
String.  Optional.  The user's biography.  Maximum 160 characters.

@item avatar_url
String.  Optional.  URL of the user's avatar image.
@end table

@deffn POST /api/users/@{username@}/block
Block a user.
@end deffn

@subheading Authentication

Requires authentication.

@deffn POST /api/users/@{username@}/mute
Mute a user.
@end deffn

@subheading Authentication

Requires authentication.

@node Post Endpoints
@section Post Endpoints

@deffn GET /api/posts
Get a paginated list of posts.
@end deffn

@subheading Authentication

Not required.

@subheading Query Parameters

@table @asis
@item page
Integer.  Page number.  Defaults to 1.

@item limit
Integer.  Items per page.  Defaults to 20, maximum 100.
@end table

@deffn POST /api/posts
Create a new post.
@end deffn

@subheading Authentication

Requires authentication.  CSRF token required.

@subheading Request Body

@table @asis
@item content
String.  Required.  The post content.  Maximum 280 characters.

@item media_urls
Array of strings.  Optional.  URLs of attached media.

@item reply_to_id
Integer.  Optional.  The ID of the post being replied to.

@item community_id
Integer.  Optional.  The ID of the community to post in.
@end table

@subheading Response

Returns the created post with status @code{201 Created}.

@deffn GET /api/posts/@{id@}
Get a specific post.
@end deffn

@subheading Authentication

Not required.

@deffn DELETE /api/posts/@{id@}
Delete a post.
@end deffn

@subheading Authentication

Requires authentication.  CSRF token required.  You may only delete
your own posts.

@deffn POST /api/posts/@{id@}/like
Like a post.
@end deffn

@subheading Authentication

Requires authentication.  CSRF token required.

@deffn DELETE /api/posts/@{id@}/like
Unlike a post.
@end deffn

@subheading Authentication

Requires authentication.  CSRF token required.

@deffn POST /api/posts/@{id@}/repost
Repost a post.
@end deffn

@subheading Authentication

Requires authentication.  CSRF token required.

@deffn POST /api/posts/@{id@}/bookmark
Bookmark a post for later.
@end deffn

@subheading Authentication

Requires authentication.  CSRF token required.

@node Timeline Endpoints
@section Timeline Endpoints

@deffn GET /api/timeline
Get the authenticated user's personalized timeline.
@end deffn

@subheading Authentication

Requires authentication.

@subheading Description

Returns posts from users that the authenticated user follows, in
reverse chronological order.

@deffn GET /api/timeline/explore
Get trending and popular posts.
@end deffn

@subheading Authentication

Not required.

@subheading Description

Returns a curated selection of popular posts for discovery.

@node Notification Endpoints
@section Notification Endpoints

@deffn GET /api/notifications
Get the authenticated user's notifications.
@end deffn

@subheading Authentication

Requires authentication.

@subheading Response

@example
@{
  "notifications": [
    @{
      "id": 1,
      "type": "like",
      "actor_username": "janedoe",
      "post_id": 123,
      "read": false,
      "created_at": "2024-01-15T10:30:00Z"
    @}
  ],
  "status": "success"
@}
@end example

@subheading Notification Types

@table @asis
@item like
Someone liked one of your posts.

@item follow
Someone followed you.

@item mention
Someone mentioned you in a post.

@item comment
Someone commented on your post.

@item repost
Someone reposted your post.
@end table

@deffn POST /api/notifications/read-all
Mark all notifications as read.
@end deffn

@subheading Authentication

Requires authentication.  CSRF token required.

@node Search Endpoints
@section Search Endpoints

@deffn GET /api/search/users
Search for users by username.
@end deffn

@subheading Authentication

Not required.

@subheading Query Parameters

@table @asis
@item q
String.  Required.  The search query.

@item page
Integer.  Page number.  Defaults to 1.

@item limit
Integer.  Items per page.  Defaults to 20.
@end table

@deffn GET /api/search/posts
Search for posts by content.
@end deffn

@subheading Authentication

Not required.

@subheading Query Parameters

Same as @code{/api/search/users}.

@node Community Endpoints
@section Community Endpoints

@deffn GET /api/communities
List all communities.
@end deffn

@subheading Authentication

Not required.

@deffn POST /api/communities
Create a new community.
@end deffn

@subheading Authentication

Requires authentication.  CSRF token required.

@subheading Request Body

@table @asis
@item name
String.  Required.  The community name.  Unique.

@item description
String.  Optional.  A description of the community.
@end table

@deffn POST /api/communities/@{id@}/join
Join a community.
@end deffn

@subheading Authentication

