@node Poll Endpoints
@section Poll Endpoints

@deffn POST /api/polls/@{id@}/vote
Vote on a poll.
@end deffn

@subheading Authentication

Requires authentication.  CSRF token required.

@subheading Request Body

@table @asis
@item option_id
Integer.  Required.  The ID of the chosen option.
@end table

@deffn GET /api/polls/@{id@}/results
Get poll results.
@end deffn

@subheading Authentication

Not required.

@subheading Response

@example
@{
  "poll_id": 1,
  "total_votes": 100,
  "options": [
    @{
      "id": 1,
      "text": "Option A",
      "votes": 60,
      "percentage": 60.0
    @},
    @{
      "id": 2,
      "text": "Option B",
      "votes": 40,
      "percentage": 40.0
    @}
  ],
  "status": "success"
@}
@end example

@node Media Endpoints
@section Media Endpoints

@deffn POST /api/media/upload
Upload an image or video.
@end deffn

@subheading Authentication

Requires authentication.  CSRF token required.

@subheading Request

The request must use @code{multipart/form-data} encoding with the file
in a field named @code{file}.

@subheading Response

Returns the URL of the uploaded file:

@example
@{
  "url": "/media/abc123.jpg",
  "status": "success"
@}
@end example

@subheading Limits

The maximum file size is 10 megabytes.  Supported formats depend on
server configuration.

@deffn GET /media/@{path@}
Serve an uploaded media file.
@end deffn

@subheading Authentication

Not required, but access may be restricted based on content.

@node Health Check
@section Health Check

@deffn GET /api/health
Check if the service is running.
@end deffn

@subheading Authentication

Not required.

@subheading Response

@example
@{
  "status": "ok",
  "service": "xeetapus"
@}
@end example

Use this endpoint for load balancer health checks and monitoring.

